.TH "__hw_addr_sync_dev" 9 "__hw_addr_sync_dev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__hw_addr_sync_dev \- Synchonize device's multicast list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __hw_addr_sync_dev
.BI "(struct netdev_hw_addr_list *list "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "int (*sync)(struct net_device *, const unsigned char *) "  ","
.BI "int (*unsync)(struct net_device *, const unsigned char *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "list" 12
address list to syncronize
.IP "dev" 12
device to sync
.IP "sync" 12
function to call if address should be added
.IP "unsync" 12
function to call if address should be removed

This funciton is intended to be called from the ndo_set_rx_mode
function of devices that require explicit address add/remove
notifications.  The unsync function may be NULL in which case
the addresses requiring removal will simply be removed without
any notification to the device.
